{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BYeS6AbYS9gzm8qnDRZVNv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the current configuration:\n\nCurrent settings in `mongod-config` ConfigMap:\n- `systemLog.verbosity: 1` → increase by 1 → new value: **2**\n- `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs: 200` → 2x → new value: **400**\n- `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor: zlib` → change to **snappy**\n\nThe StatefulSet uses a rolling update strategy, which is good. I need to:\n1. Update the ConfigMap with these three changes\n2. Trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet pods so they pick up the new configuration\n\nSince Kubernetes doesn't automatically restart pods when a ConfigMap changes, I'll use `kubectl rollout restart` to force the StatefulSet to cycle through its pods one at a time. This rolling approach maintains replica set availability throughout the update.\n\nA rolling restart will eventually cycle through the primary as well, which will trigger a brief election, but that's expected and acceptable. Let me start by updating the ConfigMap.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2352,"cache_read_input_tokens":28763,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2352},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e15c427c-f4b5-4209-9223-8a1b5fc017c6","uuid":"b447df9f-abcc-4a75-a5cd-06fff5ebf0f4","request_id":"req_011Cc81t5T3tJZ4B1XhzdEKa"}
